  "output": "## Test Coverage Analysis — jobsquare\n\n**Baseline: 0% coverage.** No `tests/` directory, no pytest (or any test framework) in `requirements.txt`, no CI workflow. All ~1,500 lines across `models.py`, `filters.py`, `store.py`, `pipeline.py`, `notify.py`, `fetchers.py`, `agent.py`, `cli.py` are completely untested. I read every module directly to verify this and to confirm the specific gaps/bugs below.\n\n**Suggested `requirements-dev.txt`:**\n```\npytest>=8.0\npytest-asyncio>=0.24\nrespx>=0.21        # mock httpx at the transport layer (fetchers.py, notify.py)\nfreezegun>=1.5      # freeze \"now\" for posted_at/filter cutoff tests\n```\nLayout: `tests/conftest.py` + one `test_<module>.py` per module + `tests/integration/test_end_to_end.py`.\n\n---\n\n### 1. `models.py` — `parse_posted_at`, `Job.key/content_hash/to_row`\n\nGaps: epoch ms-vs-seconds branch, ISO `Z`-suffix handling, unparseable Workday prose, hash excludes `posted_at`/`salary_range` (so re-timestamping doesn't trigger a \"changed\" diff — verify this is intentional).\n\n```python\n# tests/test_models.py\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import timezone\nfrom models import Job, parse_posted_at\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"raw\", [\"\", None, \"   \"])\ndef test_parse_posted_at_empty_returns_none(raw):\n    assert parse_posted_at(raw) is None\n\ndef test_parse_posted_at_epoch_milliseconds_lever_style():\n    dt = parse_posted_at(\"1643241332430\")\n    assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc and dt.year == 2022\n\ndef test_parse_posted_at_epoch_seconds():\n    assert parse_posted_at(\"1643241332\").year == 2022\n\ndef test_parse_posted_at_boundary_1e12_ms_cutoff():\n    # 12-digit value is treated as SECONDS (bug-prone edge, worth locking in)\n    assert parse_posted_at(\"999999999999\").year > 33000\n    assert parse_posted_at(\"1000000000000\").year == 2001\n\ndef test_parse_posted_at_iso_with_z_suffix():\n    assert parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:00:00Z\").tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\ndef test_parse_posted_at_iso_naive_gets_utc_attached():\n    assert parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:00:00\").tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\ndef test_parse_posted_at_workday_prose_is_unparseable():\n    assert parse_posted_at(\"Posted 3 Days Ago\") is None\n\ndef test_job_key_is_stable_identity():\n    j = Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"42\", title=\"X\", url=\"u\")\n    assert j.key == \"greenhouse:acme:42\"\n\ndef test_content_hash_changes_on_title_location_url_department():\n    base = dict(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", url=\"u\")\n    assert (Job(title=\"Engineer\", location=\"NY\", **base).content_hash\n            != Job(title=\"Senior Engineer\", location=\"NY\", **base).content_hash)\n\ndef test_content_hash_stable_when_only_posted_at_changes():\n    base = dict(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"Eng\", url=\"u\", location=\"NY\")\n    assert (Job(posted_at=\"2024-01-01\", **base).content_hash\n            == Job(posted_at=\"2024-02-01\", **base).content_hash)  # documents current behavior\n\ndef test_to_row_drops_raw_and_adds_key_and_hash():\n    j = Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"T\", url=\"u\", raw={\"secret\": 1})\n    row = j.to_row()\n    assert \"raw\" not in row and row[\"key\"] == j.key and row[\"content_hash\"] == j.content_hash\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. `filters.py` — `match`, `filter_jobs`\n\nGaps: word-boundary regex semantics, exclude/include precedence, unparseable-date fail-open behavior.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_filters.py\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\nfrom models import Job\nfrom filters import match, filter_jobs\n\ndef _job(**kw): return Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"\", url=\"u\", **kw)\n\ndef test_word_boundary_prevents_substring_match():\n    assert match(_job(title=\"Engineering Manager\"), include=[\"eng\"]) is False\n\ndef test_exclude_takes_precedence_over_include():\n    assert match(_job(title=\"Senior Intern Engineer\"), include=[\"engineer\"], exclude=[\"intern\"]) is False\n\ndef test_locations_substring_case_insensitive():\n    assert match(_job(location=\"San Francisco, CA\"), locations=[\"san francisco\"]) is True\n\ndef test_cutoff_keeps_unparseable_posted_at_rather_than_dropping():\n    j = _job(posted_at=\"Posted 3 Days Ago\")\n    assert match(j, cutoff=datetime.now(timezone.utc)) is True\n\ndef test_regex_special_characters_in_keywords_are_escaped():\n    assert match(_job(title=\"C++ Developer\"), include=[\"C++\"]) is True  # would raise pre-re.escape\n\ndef test_filter_jobs_applies_max_age_days_as_cutoff():\n    stale = _job(posted_at=(datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=30)).isoformat())\n    fresh = _job(posted_at=datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat())\n    result = filter_jobs([stale, fresh], {\"max_age_days\": 7})\n    assert fresh in result and stale not in result\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. `store.py` — `Store.diff`, `_migrate`, `added_since`, meta\n\nGaps: new/changed/unchanged diff paths, additive column migration on a legacy DB, `added_since` boundary exclusivity, duplicate keys within one `diff()` call.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_store.py\nimport sqlite3\nfrom models import Job\nfrom store import Store\n\ndef _job(ext_id=\"1\", title=\"T\", **kw):\n    return Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=ext_id, title=title, url=\"u\", **kw)\n\ndef test_diff_first_seen_is_new(tmp_path):\n    with Store(tmp_path / \"t.db\") as s:\n        new, changed = s.diff([_job()])\n        assert len(new) == 1 and changed == [] and s.count() == 1\n\ndef test_diff_unchanged_reports_neither(tmp_path):\n    with Store(tmp_path / \"t.db\") as s:\n        s.diff([_job()])\n        assert s.diff([_job()]) == ([], [])\n\ndef test_diff_changed_content_hash_reports_changed(tmp_path):\n    with Store(tmp_path / \"t.db\") as s:\n        s.diff([_job(title=\"Engineer\")])\n        new, changed = s.diff([_job(title=\"Senior Engineer\")])\n        assert new == [] and len(changed) == 1\n\ndef test_migrate_adds_salary_range_to_legacy_schema(tmp_path):\n    path = tmp_path / \"legacy.db\"\n    conn = sqlite3.connect(path)\n    conn.execute(\"\"\"CREATE TABLE jobs (key TEXT PRIMARY KEY, source TEXT, company TEXT,\n        external_id TEXT, title TEXT, url TEXT, location TEXT, department TEXT,\n        employment_type TEXT, posted_at TEXT, content_hash TEXT, first_seen TEXT, last_seen TEXT)\"\"\")\n    conn.commit(); conn.close()\n    with Store(path) as s:\n        cols = {r[\"name\"] for r in s.conn.execute(\"PRAGMA table_info(jobs)\")}\n        assert \"salary_range\" in cols\n\ndef test_added_since_is_strictly_after_boundary(tmp_path):\n    with Store(tmp_path / \"t.db\") as s:\n        s.diff([_job()])\n        boundary = s.added_since(\"2024-01-01T00:00:00+00:00\")[0][\"first_seen\"]\n        assert s.added_since(boundary) == []  # exclusive\n\ndef test_get_meta_missing_key_returns_none(tmp_path):\n    with Store(tmp_path / \"t.db\") as s:\n        assert s.get_meta(\"nope\") is None\n\ndef test_diff_duplicate_key_within_same_batch_does_not_crash(tmp_path):\n    with Store(tmp_path / \"t.db\") as s:\n        dup = _job(ext_id=\"1\")\n        new, changed = s.diff([dup, dup])  # defines expected behavior for a batch with dupes\n        assert len(new) + len(changed) <= 2\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. `notify.py` — env-var gating, `dispatch` isolation\n\n```python\n# tests/test_notify.py\nimport httpx, pytest, respx\nfrom models import Job\nimport notify\n\ndef _job(**kw): return Job(source=\"s\", company=\"Acme\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"Engineer\", url=\"https://x/1\", **kw)\n\ndef test_notify_slack_noop_when_env_unset(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.delenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", raising=False)\n    notify.notify_slack([_job()], [])  # must not raise or hit network\n\n@respx.mock\ndef test_notify_slack_posts_when_configured(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", \"https://hooks.slack.com/x\")\n    route = respx.post(\"https://hooks.slack.com/x\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(200))\n    notify.notify_slack([_job()], [])\n    assert route.called\n\n@respx.mock\ndef test_notify_sms_raises_on_twilio_error(monkeypatch):\n    for k, v in dict(TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=\"sid\", TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=\"tok\",\n                      TWILIO_FROM=\"+1\", TWILIO_TO=\"+2\").items():\n        monkeypatch.setenv(k, v)\n    respx.post(url__regex=r\".*Messages\\.json\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(401))\n    with pytest.raises(httpx.HTTPStatusError):\n        notify.notify_sms([_job()], [])\n\ndef test_sms_body_truncates_after_limit():\n    jobs = [_job(external_id=str(i)) for i in range(12)]\n    assert \"+4 more\" in notify._sms_body(jobs, [], limit=8)\n\ndef test_dispatch_isolates_notifier_failures(monkeypatch, capsys):\n    def boom(new, changed): raise RuntimeError(\"smtp down\")\n    monkeypatch.setattr(notify, \"NOTIFIERS\", [boom, notify.notify_console])\n    notify.dispatch([_job()], [])  # must not propagate\n    assert \"notifier boom failed\" in capsys.readouterr().out\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. `fetchers.py` — largest gap (15 ATS integrations, retry wrapper, pagination)\n\n**Real bug worth a test:** `_request`'s except clause is `(httpx.TransportError, httpx.HTTPStatusError)` — but `raise_for_status()` on a **permanent** 404/401/403 also raises `HTTPStatusError`, so non-transient errors get retried needlessly (`fetchers.py:37-46`).\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetchers.py\nimport json, httpx, pytest, respx\nfrom fetchers import (_request, parse_greenhouse, _lever_salary, parse_ashby,\n    _amazon_posted_at, parse_amazon, _extract_ds1, _ds1_posted_at, parse_google,\n    parse_deshaw, fetch_workday, fetch_meta, fetch_source, fetch_all, FETCHERS)\n\n@respx.mock\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_request_retries_on_transient_5xx_then_succeeds():\n    route = respx.get(\"https://x/y\").mock(side_effect=[httpx.Response(503), httpx.Response(200, json={})])\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        r = await _request(client, \"https://x/y\", retries=3)\n    assert r.status_code == 200 and route.call_count == 2\n\n@respx.mock\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_request_wastes_retries_on_permanent_404():\n    # documents the bug: a 404 should fail fast, not retry `retries` times\n    route = respx.get(\"https://x/y\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(404))\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        with pytest.raises(RuntimeError):\n            await _request(client, \"https://x/y\", retries=2)\n    assert route.call_count == 2\n\ndef test_lever_salary_prefers_range_over_description():\n    assert _lever_salary({\"salaryRange\": {\"min\": 100000, \"max\": 150000, \"currency\": \"USD\"}}) \\\n        == \"USD 100,000–150,000\"\n\ndef test_parse_ashby_skips_unlisted_jobs():\n    assert parse_ashby(\"acme\", {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": \"1\", \"isListed\": False}]}) == []\n\ndef test_amazon_posted_at_parses_us_format():\n    assert _amazon_posted_at(\"June 26, 2026\") == \"2026-06-26T00:00:00+00:00\"\n\ndef test_amazon_posted_at_handles_malformed_value():\n    assert _amazon_posted_at(\"garbage\") == \"\"\n\ndef test_extract_ds1_returns_empty_on_malformed_json():\n    assert _extract_ds1(\"key: 'ds:1', data:[not valid json] ,sideChannel\") == []\n\ndef test_parse_deshaw_dedups_repeated_cards():\n    page = ('<div data-job-id=\"123\" class=\"job-display-name\">Eng</div>' * 2)\n    assert len(parse_deshaw(\"deshaw\", page)) == 1\n\n@respx.mock\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_workday_stops_on_empty_postings():\n    respx.post(url__regex=r\".*/jobs\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(200, json={\"jobPostings\": [], \"total\": 0}))\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        assert await fetch_workday(client, {\"host\": \"h\", \"tenant\": \"t\", \"site\": \"s\"}) == []\n\n@respx.mock\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_meta_raises_on_graphql_errors_documenting_doc_id_rotation():\n    respx.get(\"https://www.metacareers.com/jobs\").mock(\n        return_value=httpx.Response(200, text='[\"LSD\",[],{\"token\":\"tok\"}] \"__spin_r\":1'))\n    respx.post(\"https://www.metacareers.com/graphql\").mock(\n        return_value=httpx.Response(200, text='for (;;);' + json.dumps({\"errors\": [{\"message\": \"doc_id rotated\"}]})))\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"doc_id rotated\"):\n            await fetch_meta(client, {\"company\": \"meta\"})\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_source_unknown_ats_raises_valueerror():\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"unknown ATS\"):\n            await fetch_source(client, {\"ats\": \"bogus\"})\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_all_isolates_one_failing_source(monkeypatch, capsys):\n    async def boom(client, source): raise RuntimeError(\"network down\")\n    async def ok(client, source): return [object()]\n    monkeypatch.setitem(FETCHERS, \"greenhouse\", boom)\n    monkeypatch.setitem(FETCHERS, \"lever\", ok)\n    jobs = await fetch_all([{\"ats\": \"greenhouse\", \"company\": \"a\"}, {\"ats\": \"lever\", \"company\": \"b\"}])\n    assert len(jobs) == 1\n    assert \"greenhouse:a failed\" in capsys.readouterr().out\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. `pipeline.py`\n\n```python\n# tests/test_pipeline.py\nfrom pipeline import load_config\n\ndef test_load_config_applies_defaults(tmp_path):\n    p = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"; p.write_text(\"sources: []\\n\")\n    cfg = load_config(p)\n    assert cfg[\"filters\"] == {} and cfg[\"db\"] == \"jobs.db\" and cfg[\"concurrency\"] == 8\n\n# missing: run() dry_run vs persisted paths — needs fetch_all/dispatch mocked\nasync def test_run_dry_run_does_not_touch_store(tmp_path, monkeypatch): ...\nasync def test_run_persists_and_dispatches_when_not_dry_run(tmp_path, monkeypatch): ...\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. `agent.py`\n\n**Real gap, not just missing test:** `cmd_pdf_render` calls `subprocess.run(..., timeout=120)` with no `except subprocess.TimeoutExpired` (`agent.py:222-226`) — a hung Chrome render currently crashes with a traceback instead of the clean `return 1` used for every other render failure.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_agent.py\nfrom agent import cmd_db_mark, _normalize_ats, cmd_pdf_render, _chrome_bin\n\ndef test_db_mark_rejects_invalid_watermark(capsys):\n    assert cmd_db_mark([\"not-a-timestamp\"]) == 2\n\ndef test_normalize_ats_skips_replacements_inside_style_and_script():\n    html = \"<style>.x{content:'\\u2014'}</style><script>var x='\\u2014';</script><p>\\u2014</p>\"\n    out, counts = _normalize_ats(html)\n    assert counts[\"em-dash\"] == 1  # only the <p> occurrence, not style/script\n\ndef test_pdf_render_missing_input_returns_2(tmp_path):\n    assert cmd_pdf_render([str(tmp_path / \"missing.html\")]) == 2\n\ndef test_pdf_render_handles_subprocess_timeout_gracefully(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n    import subprocess\n    src = tmp_path / \"in.html\"; src.write_text(\"<html></html>\")\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"agent._chrome_bin\", lambda: \"/bin/true\")\n    def raise_timeout(*a, **k): raise subprocess.TimeoutExpired(cmd=\"chrome\", timeout=120)\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"subprocess.run\", raise_timeout)\n    rc = cmd_pdf_render([str(src)])\n    assert rc == 1  # currently raises unhandled instead\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. `cli.py`\n\n```python\n# tests/test_cli.py\nfrom cli import main\n\ndef test_cli_passes_dry_run_flag_through(monkeypatch):\n    calls = {}\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"cli.run_sync\", lambda config, dry_run: calls.update(config=config, dry_run=dry_run))\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"sys.argv\", [\"cli.py\", \"-c\", \"custom.yaml\", \"--dry-run\"])\n    main()\n    assert calls == {\"config\": \"custom.yaml\", \"dry_run\": True}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 9. Integration gaps (nothing covered end-to-end today)\n\n```python\n# tests/integration/test_end_to_end.py\nasync def test_full_pipeline_first_run_then_rerun_only_surfaces_deltas(tmp_path, respx_mock):\n    \"\"\"Mock a greenhouse endpoint -> run() twice with one job changed/one added ->\n    assert new/changed split and store.count() reflect the delta correctly.\"\"\"\n\nasync def test_scan_marker_roundtrip_via_agent_db_new_and_db_mark(tmp_path, capsys):\n    \"\"\"cmd_db_new (no marker) -> since-days window; cmd_db_mark(watermark) ->\n    cmd_db_new again -> only rows strictly after the watermark returned.\"\"\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Priority ranking\n1. **`store.py` diff logic** + **`fetchers.py` parse_\\* normalizers** — highest risk (silent dedup/data corruption), cheapest to test (pure functions).\n2. **`filters.py`** — small and pure, but exclude/include precedence and word-boundary matching are genuinely non-obvious; lock in before someone \"simplifies\" it away.\n3. **`fetchers.py` retry wrapper** — the 4xx-gets-retried bug is real; a test forces a decision either way.\n4. **`notify.py` dispatch isolation** + **`agent.py` PDF timeout** — both are user-visible error-handling gaps.\n5. Bespoke scrapers (Google/D.E. Shaw/Two Sigma/Meta) — better served by a periodic live smoke test than frozen fixtures since they depend on upstream markup, but their pure `parse_*` functions should still get fixture coverage.\n\nWant me to scaffold `tests/` with these skeletons and wire up `pytest` + `respx` so they actually run?\n",
